1.  For each peer-server pair generate a unique identifiers for peer and server and include that in handshake . 
    goal is to replace peer lookup based on ip with peer look up based on identifier, 
    this will ensure vpn works even if client ip address changes.

2.  Rekeying. generate new key pair after every x mins or y packets. Store old key pair to decrypt late packets. Ensures forward secrecy.

3.  Add packet counters for replay protection.

4.  Add timers on each peer for last handshake, last sent, last rec. Used for rekeying, identifying stale sessions, or send keepalives
    on server last packet sent -> decides keepalives
    on server last packet received -> decides stale session
    on server(or client) last hanshake -> decides time for rehandshake and rekey 

5. Add states on client side too



